  <static seed="109" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/MixedNumberMultiplicationWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>A cake recipe needs <m>{3{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> cups of flour. Using this recipe, to bake <m>6</m> cakes, how many cups of flour are needed?</p>
<p>To bake <m>6</m> cakes, <fillin characters="9" name="AnSwEr0001"/> cups of flour are needed.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>21</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>Each cake needs <m>{3{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}}</m> cups of flour. To find how many cups of flour are needed to bake <m>6</m> cakes, we use multiplication:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {3{\textstyle\frac{1}{2}}} \cdot 6
      \amp = \frac{7}{2} \cdot \frac{6}{1} \\
      \amp = \frac{7}{1} \cdot \frac{3}{1} \\
      \amp = \frac{21}{1} \\
      \amp = {21}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>To bake <m>6</m> cakes, <m>{21}</m> cups of flour are needed.</p>
</solution>
